  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support the World Bank in co-hosting the REDD Partnership Secretariat</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The BMU promoted the REDD+ Partnership of the World Bank with a grant of 800,000 &#x20AC;. This partnership was founded in 2010 and aimed at strengthening the cooperation between donor and REDD+ countries as well as advancing the development of a REDD+ mechanism. Within this partnership, Germany mainly supported the inclusion of Safeguards and the participation of civil society representatives. Main tasks included developing a voluntary database for a better coordination and improving the exchange of experiences on REDD+. The REDD+ Partnership ended with the inclusion of a REDD+ mechanism in the successor of the Kyoto Protocol which was adopted at the COP 2015 in Paris.</narrative>
  </description>
